# Decisions List / Content Browser

## Overview
Create the canonical, project-wide Decisions List / Content Browser for Archject that presents every decision in a clear, organized, and actionable way. The page supports robust filters, bulk actions (share links, export, change status), quick previews, and seamless integration with the surrounding decision workflow (CRUD, templates, and dashboards). It should be visually consistent with the project’s design system, accessible, mobile-friendly, and scalable to handle large project ecosystems with multiple decisions, documents, and comments.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A central, canonical list of all decisions across a project, presented as a searchable, filterable, and bulk-action-enabled content browser. Each decision is a self-contained object with metadata, options, status, due dates, associated files, comments, and client-facing share links.

Goals:
- Provide fast, full-text search and faceted filters across projects, decisions, files, and comments.
- Enable bulk actions: share client links, export decision data (PDF/CSV/JSON), and bulk status changes (e.g., move multiple decisions from draft to pending or approved).
- Offer quick preview: hover or select a decision to view essential details (summary, options, status, due date, linked files, client link, recent activity) without navigating away.
- Promote faster decision creation via templates and an integrated Create button that leverages the Decision Templates Library.
- Maintain an audit-friendly, time-stamped history and linkage to the Edit / Manage Decision Page for deep editing and versioning.

Connected features:
- Search & Filter Functionality: Full-text search across decisions, projects, files, and comments; faceted filters by status, assignee, date ranges, template type, priority, requester/client status, and tags.
- Decision Objects CRUD: Create, read, update, delete Decision Objects, including options, metadata, and status transitions (draft, pending, approved, rejected). Include per-decision history, change tracking, and versioning hooks for re-issues.
- Decision Templates Library: Library of opinionated templates for common decision types (finishes, layouts, change requests) to accelerate decision creation with pre-filled options, metadata fields, and default status transitions.

UI elements and how they need to look:
- Filter Bar: status (tags), assignee, date range, template type, search box with autosuggest; quick filters for “My Decisions,” “Awaiting Client,” and “Overdue.”
- Decisions Table/Card: per-row or per-card representation showing title, status badge, due date, linked files count, client share link icon, last updated timestamp, and quick action row (edit, duplicate, delete, share).
- Bulk Actions Bar: appears when one or more items are selected; options include Export, Share Links, Change Status, Assign, Remove, and Delete (with confirm).
- Preview Pane: floating or docked pane that shows a quick view of the selected decision with sections for Summary, Key Options, Metadata, Activity, and a link to Open in Manage/Edit page.
- Create Decision Button: prominent, pill-shaped primary action, opening a modal or side panel to create a decision (with metadata, options, and initial status).
- Templates Quick Insert: a panel or dropdown to apply templates during create or via the editor.
- Client Share Links: indicator/icon per decision with copy/share actions and link status (active/expired).

Visual guidance:
- Use the project’s design system: clean white cards, soft shadows, 12–16px radii, ample whitespace, and gentle color accents for statuses. Primary actions use deep green (#195C4A). Success indicators use bright green (#7BE495). Warnings use yellow/orange tones; errors use light red. All typography adheres to the standardized font family and weights.

Connected Pages:
- Dashboard: User-specific overview with decisions awaiting client response and quick actions to create or share client links.
- Edit / Manage Decision Page: Detailed editing with history, version comparison, and reissue share link capability.

API integrations:
- No external APIs required for this task; all data interactions will be via the project’s internal API surface.

## Components to Build
- DecisionsListContainer: Grid/list wrapper for responsive rendering, handles pagination, virtualized scrolling for large datasets.
- FilterBar: UI for text search, multi-selects, range pickers, and quick filters; emits filter state to parent.
- DecisionsTable/Card: Card-based or tabular representation with responsive columns; includes status badge, due date, counts, and action icons.
- PreviewPane: Read-only quick view or interactive mini-editor for summary and metadata; supports hover/selection triggers.
- BulkActionsBar: Top/side bar that enables bulk operations; includes confirm dialogs for destructive actions.
- CreateDecisionModal / CreateDecisionPanel: Form-based creation surface with validation, supports templates integration.
- EditDecisionPageLink: Route or button to navigate to the dedicated Edit / Manage Decision Page.
- TemplatesLibraryPanel: Browse and apply templates; supports searching, filtering, and “Apply template” action.
- ShareLinkManager: UI and logic to generate, copy, and manage client-facing share links (active/expired).
- HistoryPanel: Lightweight view of decision history within the Edit page; for the list view, show last activity snippet.

Technical details for components:
- Each component should be designed with accessibility (A11y) in mind: proper roles, keyboard navigation, ARIA labels, and screen-reader friendly labels.
- State management: Use a centralized store (Redux/Context) or a modern hook-based approach with a clear schema for decisions, templates, filters, and UI state (loading, error, success).

